It was one of those climbs. I was cycling in Tuscany, coming over the crop of hills that stands between Viareggio and Lucca and I'd miscalculated my gearing; as the bike ran out of gears I struggled to turn my legs over on a particularly steep switchback and as I did so an Alfa Romeo came round the bend. "Bravo," yelled the driver, gesticulating and grinning, "bravo". And, in that moment of peak Italy, my body found the extra gear that the bike was missing.

